  "prompt": "How long can a milkshake last out of the fridge?",
  "response": "A milkshake's lifespan outside the fridge is unfortunately pretty short. **It's generally best to consume a milkshake within 1-2 hours if it's left at room temperature (around 70\u00b0F or 21\u00b0C).**\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Dairy Products:** Milkshakes are primarily made with dairy products (milk and ice cream), which are prone to bacterial growth when left at room temperature.\n*   **Temperature Danger Zone:** Bacteria multiply rapidly in the \"temperature danger zone,\" which is between 40\u00b0F (4\u00b0C) and 140\u00b0F (60\u00b0C). Milkshakes fall squarely into this range when left out.\n*   **Ingredients:** Other ingredients like fruit, syrups, or whipped cream can also contribute to spoilage.\n\n**After 2 hours, the risk of bacterial contamination increases significantly, which could lead to food poisoning.** You might not be able to see or smell the spoilage, but the bacteria could still be present.\n\n**Factors that might affect the spoilage rate:**\n\n*   **Ambient Temperature:** A hot day will cause it to spoil much faster.\n*   **Ingredients:** Some ingredients spoil faster than others.\n*   **Hygiene:** How clean the milkshake was prepared.\n\n**In summary, to be safe, don't leave a milkshake out of the fridge for more than 1-2 hours. If in doubt, throw it out!**\n",
